CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 1, 1956, pg. A11 reads: " 'Contestants - These pretty young ladies were finalists, but lost to Mildred Ann Briscoe in "Miss WILY" contest. Left to right: Barbara M. Robinson, Greta Jean Leach, Mavourneen Reynolds and Marjorie Parker, all of whom hold RCA Victor clock radios, consolation prizes. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of "Miss WILY" contestant finalists, from left: Barbara M. Robinson, Greta Jean Leach, Mavourneen Reynolds, and Marjorie Parker, holding clock radios, posed in Warner's Cinerama Theatre
